The Managing Director, Heritage Bank Plc, Ifie Sekibo has said that with partnership, truth, character and rigorous commitment to businesses, the micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs) have the potential of repositioning the nation’s economy on the path of sustainable growth. Sekibo disclosed this while speaking during a webinar session, a virtual conference platform at the Upgrade Summit 2020, on the theme, “Converting Ideas into Reality with Focus on SME’s.” He said evidences had shown that for SMEs to continue to survive and remain the bedrock of any vibrant economy, the players must continuously reinvent themselves, complement each other, dream big, possess cutting edge ideas and think and rethink before venturing into businesses. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Heritage Bank MD urges banks to drive SMEs Nigeria must support SMEs, agric to move away from poverty  – Heritage Bank boss Sekibo seeks more support for MSMEs to boost GDP